&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Bank Registered Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;(flexible and long-term opportunities available)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hertfordshire Community NHS Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations covered: &lt;/strong&gt;Herts and Essex Hospital, &lt;/span&gt;Haymeads Ln, Bishop&#39;s Stortford CM23 5JH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Danesbury Neurological Centre, &lt;/span&gt;73 School Ln, Welwyn AL6 9SB&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Queen Victoria Memorial Hospital,&lt;/span&gt; School Ln, Welwyn AL6 9PW&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Pay rates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fringe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Day: £16.44&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Night/Sat: £18.93 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sun/Bank Holiday: £23.13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;‘Earlies’, ‘Lates’, ‘Days’, ‘Nights’ &amp; ‘Weekend’ bank shift patterns available. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Times as follows: 07.30-14.00, 14.00-19.45, 19.30-07.45&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hertfordshire Community NHS Trust are proud of the wide range of general and specialist services that they can provide to the local community. They employ over 3000 dedicated staff making sure patients get the best care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and highly motivated Band 5 Registered Nurses to work Bank shifts throughout Hertfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work within a team to promote and provide high quality care and have excellent interpersonal communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for a post, you &lt;strong&gt;must&lt;/strong&gt; have a minimum of 6 months experience in a similar role held within the last 2 years and be &lt;strong&gt;NMC&lt;/strong&gt; registered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to giving you more flexibility and control over your working life. By joining the NHSP bank you will gain access to the best choice of available shifts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return for your hard work and your professional, caring, and reliable service you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive, weekly pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Priority access to available shifts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to the NHSP Stakeholder Pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paid annual leave, statutory maternity pays (subject to qualifying criteria)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training and development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First choice of shifts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Uniform and other workplace benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be regularly informed via email of the recruitment process, so please check your emails regularly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Though we endeavor to do so, we regret that we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
